    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="605"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/407.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">Davis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department informed that cases of gourdes have arrived and are arriving from New
                    York and that these are being signed and placed in circulation by the board of
                    verification. To July 10, 1915, twenty cases of two-gourde bills had arrived in
                    Haiti, according to Department’s information, and certain remittances to New
                    York lead the Department to believe that further issues are shortly to be put
                    into circulation. Consult with Admiral Caperton and take such measures as are
                    needful to secure cases of gourdes on arrival, placing them under Legation’s
                    seal until such time as you are instructed regarding their release.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
